# Coverage allowlist — packages exempt from the 95% threshold.
#
# Binding rule: CLAUDE.md → Mandatory rules → "Unit test coverage ≥95%".
#
# Format:
#   - one glob pattern per line; shell-style globs supported (* matches any).
#   - lines beginning with # are comments.
#   - blank lines ignored.
#
# Policy for adding entries:
#   1. The package MUST fall into one of these categories:
#      A. cmd/* entry point (only `main()` wiring, no business logic).
#      B. Test helper (bufconn / testutil / idptest / storetest).
#      C. DB-bound — tests require live PostgreSQL.
#      D. OS-bound — tests need kernel APIs / system keychain / packet capture.
#      E. Network-infra-bound — tests need real S3 / NATS / Redis Sentinel.
#      F. Integration-only — existing tests live behind build tags.
#   2. Each entry MUST cite the category in the trailing comment.
#   3. Adding to the allowlist requires explicit user approval.
#   4. Goal: empty allowlist. Run `scripts/check-go-coverage.sh --strict-allowlist`
#      to surface entries that have since reached the threshold and can be removed.
#
# Audit method: docs/developers/workflow/coverage-allowlist-methodology.md.
# Removed-entry history is in `git log -p scripts/.coverage-allowlist`; this
# file carries only the current live state plus a section at the bottom
# listing the canonical seam patterns proven during prior sweeps.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (A) cmd/* entry points — main() wiring, no business logic.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# (A) Service main entry points — main() that parses flags, calls boot,
# and waits on a signal. Cannot be unit-tested in isolation because they
# call os.Exit and rely on real OS signal delivery.
*/packages/agent/cmd/agent
*/packages/ai-gateway/cmd/ai-gateway
*/packages/compliance-proxy/cmd/compliance-proxy
*/packages/control-plane/cmd/control-plane
*/packages/nexus-hub/cmd/nexus-hub

# (A) cmd/*/wiring — DI assembly with measurable observable behavior. E85
# Phase 7 pushed each package as far as unit tests can reach (see D-10
# outcome table in docs/developers/specs/e85/decision-log.md). The residual
# in each package is integration-bound:
#   - agent/wiring  93.1% — D OS (keystore/keychain, Win/Linux paths),
#       E network (WS reconnect closure bodies, OAuth Run path).
#   - ai-gateway/wiring  73.4% — A `Boot` orchestrator (15-stage sequencer),
#       C DB-bound (`InitCacheLayer`, `LoadHookConfigsFromDB`, `InitQuota`,
#       `InitHookConfigCache`), E network (`InitThingClient`, `MountRoutes`
#       Prometheus duplicate-registration, `InitGeminiCacheMgrSet`,
#       `WireDiagReconnect`, `WireStaticInfoReconnect`, `InitDB`,
#       `InitMQProducer`).
#   - compliance-proxy/wiring  82.8% — C `InitCompliance` DB-bound, E network
#       (`InitThingClient`, `InitMQProducer`, `LastReportAge`,
#       `doReconnectWork`, `RunShutdown`, `WireOnReconnect`,
#       `CaptureThingClientResult`), structurally unreachable (`InitInfra`
#       NewUpstreamTransport error, cert warmup).
#   - control-plane/wiring  90.4% — C DB (`InitDB`, `runtime.go`,
#       `reconcile.go`), D OS (`authserver.go` Abs/keystore, `bootstrap.go`
#       Setenv), E network (`hub.go`, `redis.go`, `mq.go` consumer-fails),
#       structurally unreachable (3 timing/dead-code arms).
#   - nexus-hub/wiring  66.1% — C DB (`InitDB`, `InitSelfReg`,
#       `InitSelfShadow`, `InitScheduler`, `RunConfigKeyAudit`,
#       `InitSIEMBridge`), E network (`InitMQ`, `InitOTEL`,
#       `StartWSSignalSubscriber`).
# Integration coverage via /smoke-gateway --all-ingress + /test-all + the
# scenario harness covers every wiring path end-to-end.
*/packages/agent/cmd/agent/wiring
*/packages/ai-gateway/cmd/ai-gateway/wiring
*/packages/compliance-proxy/cmd/compliance-proxy/wiring
*/packages/control-plane/cmd/control-plane/wiring
*/packages/nexus-hub/cmd/nexus-hub/wiring

